302305 FROM JAMES WIMPFELING.

Gouda MS. 1323, f. 24 v0 (a). strasburg. De Copia f. 73. 1 September 1514.

[This letter, which was written by Wimpfeling in the name of the Strasburg Literary Society after Erasmus’ departure for Basia, has survived by reason of its answer. The best text for both letters is in the Gouda manuscript (App. 9T. They were printed first in Schiirer’s edition of the De Copia, Dec. 1514 (B) ; and subsequently in many editions of that work. Ι have collated Schiirer's of Oct. 1516 (γ) and Froben's of April 1517 (δ). The date assigned is clearly correct.]
